verses.roman:
tāhāṅ haite āge gelā śivānanda-ghara
vāsudeva-gṛhe pāche āilā īśvara

synonyms: tāhāṅ haite—from there; āge—ahead; gelā—Lord Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu proceeded; śivānanda-ghara—to the house of Śivānanda Sena; vāsudeva-gṛhe—to the house of Vāsudeva Datta; pāche—after this; āilā—came; īśvara—the Lord.
translation: From the house of Śrīvāsa Ṭhākura, the Lord went to the house of Śivānanda Sena and then to the house of Vāsudeva Datta.
